Role & Goal
You are a senior automation engineer. Build a weekly validation and update script that keeps Jira milestone dates aligned with a Google Sheets delivery timeline, with a required human approval step before applying updates.

Data Source: Google Sheets
I have a Google Sheet containing project timelines. Each row represents a milestone within a Train.

Columns include (order may vary):

Train identifier (examples: 2026Train1, 2026TrainAG1, but generally 2026Train*)

Milestone name (e.g. Branch Cut, Regression Signoff)

Start date

Duration (days)

End date

Quarter (e.g. 26.Q1)

Authoritative milestones per Train:

Branch Cut → expected Dev completion date

Regression Signoff → expected QA sign-off date

There may be many Trains in the sheet. The script must dynamically detect all Train identifiers and must not rely on hard-coded Train names.

Jira Requirements
Jira contains issues of type:

Epic

Feature

Each issue includes:

A Train identifier field (string match, e.g. 2026Train123)

Dev completion date field

QA sign-off date field

Validation Logic
The script runs once per week and performs the following steps:

Read the Google Sheet and build a per-Train lookup:

Branch Cut → expected Dev completion date

Regression Signoff → expected QA sign-off date

Query Jira for all Epic and Feature issues whose Train field matches any Train found in the sheet (pattern-based, not hard-coded).

For each issue:

Compare Jira Dev completion date vs Sheet Branch Cut date

Compare Jira QA sign-off date vs Sheet Regression Signoff date

Identify discrepancies where:

A Jira date is missing

A Jira date exists but does not match the sheet

Approval Workflow (Required)
The script must not update Jira automatically.

Instead:

Generate a proposed update list containing all mismatches.

Send an approval email (or similar approval mechanism) containing:

Jira issue key

Issue type

Train

Field to be updated

Current Jira value

Proposed value (from Google Sheet)

Updates to Jira should occur only after explicit human approval, such as:

Clicking an approval link

Replying “APPROVE”

Approving via Google Form / Sheet checkbox

If approval is not received, no Jira updates are made.

Execution Constraints

Script runs weekly (time-based trigger)

Handles new Trains automatically

Avoids duplicate notifications for the same unresolved mismatch

Logs all actions and approvals for auditability

Output / Reporting
Recommend and implement the most practical approach:

A Google Sheet “Validation Report” tab

Email summary of discrepancies and approvals

Each discrepancy record should include:

Jira issue key

Issue type

Train name

Field name

Expected date (from sheet)

Actual date (from Jira)

Approval status

What to Deliver
Please provide:

Recommended architecture (e.g. Google Apps Script + Jira REST API)

Assumptions about Jira fields and authentication

High-level flow diagram or step breakdown

Pseudocode or real implementation code (preferred)

Setup instructions (auth, triggers, email approval flow)

Optimize for clarity, safety (no accidental updates), and long-term maintainability.